      "content": "that's a good start. can u expand on that? specifically, i want to address the idea of meritocracy. some people say that redistribution is unfair because people should just be rewarded based on their own hard work/talent. how can i frame that meritocracy argument as being fundamentally flawed or even harmful in the context of racial equity?",
